Report for SPN01

This report shows the results for patient SPN01 of SCOUT cohort. SPN01 is a prototype micro-satellite stable (MSS) colorectal cancer composed of 4 clones SPN01 is profiled by 3 samples collected at 1 time-point.

1 Tissue Simulation and Sampling

This part of the report shows how the tumour growth in time. Muller plot and time series plot show changing in cellular growth of the different clones.

1.1 Tissue dynamics

SPN01 growth dynamics is summarized by the muller plot toghter with a temporal line showing the time in which samplig is perfomed.

1.2 Sampling

SPN01 is sampled at 1 time-point, where a total of 3 samples are derived. Sampling dynamics is reported in the following plot:

General information about the samples are reported in the table below.

2 Mutation Engine

Mutational processes are added to the sampled cells based on the tumour type. In particular, the mutation engine is set up by specifing:

  1. Mutation rates of SNVs, INDELs and CNAs;
  2. Driver SNVs and CNAs;
  3. SBS and ID mutational signatures.

2.1 Drivers event

For SPN01 drivers SNVs and CNAs are added to a particular clone, each chatacterized by a specific mutation rate. The following table summarizes the genomic and evolutionary features of the clones.

3 Sequencing results

The SPN01 is sequenced with a coverage of 100X and a simulated purity of 0.9.
